Document: NavigationLink3D
Path: godot/classes/class_navigationlink3d.rst
Summary: NavigationLink3D is a node that creates a link between two points on a navigation mesh, allowing agents to traverse between disconnected navigation regions.

Inherits: Node3D < Node < Object

NavigationLink3D is a node that creates a link between two points on a navigation mesh. It is used to connect two navigation regions that are otherwise disconnected, allowing navigation agents to move between them. The link can be bidirectional or unidirectional.

Properties:
- enabled (bool): If true, the navigation link is active and will be used by navigation agents. Default: true.
- bidirectional (bool): If true, the link can be traversed in both directions. If false, the link can only be traversed from the start position to the end position. Default: true.
- navigation_layers (int): A bitmask that determines which navigation layers this link belongs to. Navigation agents can be configured to only use links that match their navigation layers. Default: 1.
- start_position (Vector3): The starting point of the link in local coordinates. Default: Vector3(0, 0, 0).
- end_position (Vector3): The ending point of the link in local coordinates. Default: Vector3(0, 0, 0).
- enter_cost (float): When pathfinding, this value is added to the path distance when entering this link. This can be used to discourage agents from using certain links. Default: 0.0.
- travel_cost (float): When pathfinding, this value is multiplied by the distance of the link. This can be used to make certain links more or less attractive to agents. Default: 1.0.

Methods:
Method: set_global_start_position(position: Vector3) → void
Sets the starting position of the link in global coordinates.

Method: get_global_start_position() → Vector3
Returns the starting position of the link in global coordinates.

Method: set_global_end_position(position: Vector3) → void
Sets the ending position of the link in global coordinates.

Method: get_global_end_position() → Vector3
Returns the ending position of the link in global coordinates.

Key Rule: NavigationLink3D must be a child of a NavigationRegion3D or be added to a NavigationServer3D map to be functional. Changes to properties like start_position or end_position at runtime require the navigation map to be updated to reflect the change in connectivity.

GDScript:
    var link = NavigationLink3D.new()
    link.start_position = Vector3(0, 0, 0)
    link.end_position = Vector3(10, 0, 0)
    add_child(link)

C#:
    NavigationLink3D link = new NavigationLink3D();
    link.StartPosition = new Vector3(0, 0, 0);
    link.EndPosition = new Vector3(10, 0, 0);
    AddChild(link);
---CHUNK---
